.SS setup
.PP
.I Setup integration across multiple VMs
.PP
.B Category:
Fleet
.br
.B Maturity:
experimental
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-pve\-fleet setup (\-\-all | \-\-vmid VMID... | \-\-tag TAG...) [\-\-exclude VMID]... [\-\-continue\-on\-error]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B \-\-all
Process every OVMF VM
.TP
.B \-\-vmid VMID
Specific VMID (repeatable; overrides \-\-all)
.TP
.B \-\-tag TAG
Filter to VMs with Proxmox tag (repeatable)
.TP
.B \-\-exclude VMID
Exclude specific VMIDs (repeatable)
.TP
.B \-\-running\-ok
Pass \-\-running\-ok to each per\-VM setup
.TP
.B \-\-continue\-on\-error
Don\'t abort batch on first failure (default: on)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-pve\-fleet setup \-\-all
sudo lamboot\-pve\-fleet setup \-\-all \-\-tag webserver \-\-exclude 100
sudo lamboot\-pve\-fleet setup \-\-vmid 100 \-\-vmid 101
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Invokes lamboot\-pve\-setup for each target VM serially. Skips already\-set\-up VMs. v0.2 is serial; parallel mode deferred to v0.3+.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Requires root (sudo)
